        "author": {
          "name": "Amir Shehata",
          "email": "amir.shehata@intel.com",
          "date": "2018-06-26 03:59:07.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Amir Shehata",
          "email": "ashehata@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2018-08-17 20:11:46.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9120 lnet: calculate the lnd timeout",
        "message": "LU-9120 lnet: calculate the lnd timeout\n\nCalculate the LND timeout based on the transaction timeout\nand the retry count. Both of these are user defined values. Whenever\nthey are set the lnd timeout is calculated. The LNDs use these\ntimeouts instead of the LND timeout module parameter.\n\nRetry count can be set to 0, which means no retries. In that case the\nLND timeout will default to 5 seconds, which is the same as the\ndefault transaction timeout.\n\nTest-Parameters: forbuildonly\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <ashehata@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I5a37caa2b69df155211864735ba8b275fc2d34bb\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/32770\nReviewed-by: Olaf Weber <olaf.weber@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Sonia Sharma <sharmaso@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Jenkins\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/multi-rail"
    }
  },
